parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to become stuck in gear, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The transmission indicator on the dash is off
the vehicle is stuck in gear
the vehicle freezes
and the clutch pedal feels soft or spongy.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of various electronic systems can cause safety issues, such as loss of headlights, blinkers, and speedometer functionality, leading to potential accidents.
symptoms: High beam light indicator is on but low beams are on
speedometer is not working
blinkers are not working
and radio is not working.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the coil springs can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially fatal consequences.
symptoms: Popping noise and foul odor
broken coil spring
punctured tire
and loud clunking noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can lead to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates without driver input
fails to slow down when braking
and may continue to accelerate even when the brake pedal is depressed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cruise control cable failure can cause unintended acceleration, loss of vehicle control, and accidents.
symptoms: The cruise control cable gets stuck or jammed
causing the throttle to remain open
and the vehicle to accelerate without driver input.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Throttle cable housing failure can cause unintended acceleration, loss of vehicle control, and accidents.
symptoms: The throttle cable housing does not stay in its seat
causing over-acceleration
and making it difficult to stop the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose stopping power, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal goes to the floor
the vehicle does not stop immediately
the brake warning light illuminates
and the vehicle experiences vibration or shimmy when braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake hydraulic system can cause the vehicle to lose stopping power, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Brake fluid leaks
brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal goes to the floor
and the vehicle experiences vibration or shimmy when braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake master cylinder can cause the vehicle to lose stopping power, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal goes to the floor
and the vehicle experiences vibration or shimmy when braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake proportioning valve can cause the vehicle to lose stopping power, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal goes to the floor
and the vehicle experiences vibration or shimmy when braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake lights can cause other drivers to not be aware of the vehicle's intention to stop, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Brake lights do not illuminate
and the vehicle experiences vibration or shimmy when braking.
